<br>
1.  We zone into Fear with so many people we crash the zone.  Oops.  Yah, that's how many we had, call it zergling, doesn't bother me, we were having a good time.  Lot of people there on their first plane raid ever, including about a dozen non-guilded peeps.<br>
2.  We begin clearing the plane.  We're pulling large chunks of the zone at a time and aoe'ing them all.  Was a LOT of fun, everyone laughing, yada yadda...<br>
3.  The server crashes (crash 1)<br>
4.  I personaly go into IV's chat room.  I knew that with the server crash, CT would be up.  I knew that IV would want to kill CT.  I also am pretty sure that no other guild with the possible exception of CC can solo kill CT.  So, to keep from bumping heads I say &quot;Hey guys, just to let you know, we're in Fear, we have no intention of kiling CT solo or jointly, and we'll be happy to tell you when we're done if you want to come in and kill him&quot;.<br>
5.  I pop back into PO's chat channel.  Several members of IV, including befb, zaral and zhraath begin messaging me asking how long it would take us, were we clearing the whole plane, etc...<br>
6.  I tell zaral and zhraath that I wasn't sure how long, that we can't clear it as fast as them, prolly 3-4 hours, but that we would let them know when we were done, and we'd tell them first.  I had no problem with them forming up and being ready to jump when we finished.<br>
7. Zhraath approaches me with an offer: they help us clear fear so it's done faster, we get all the loot.<br>
<br>
Let me interject that this is a more than fair offer.  However, it assumes that ALL we cared about was getting the loot.  Bear in mind that there were people there for the first time who were enjoying themselves, and wanted that sense of accomplishment.  There were also PO applicants whom we wanted to see in a raid type environment.  We also had so many in zone that we already had a small lag/link death problem.  So far all of those reasons, we said thanks, but we'd like to do it ourselves.  Bottom line, doesn't matter why we said no, we said no.<br>
<br>
8.  Still in chat, rhyuu says better accept our offer 'cause if you don't we're gonna plow it anyway.<br>
9.  Server comes back up.<br>
10. 2 minutes later, server crashes again.  Back to chat.<br>
11. IV members flood our chat channel... wasn't pw protected because of the number of guests we had on the raid.  Next time it will be.  They spend the next 20 minutes justifying why they have to come into Fear while we're still there.<br>
12.  Server comes back up and we log back in, still in Fear.<br>
13.  IV enters the zone.  Jaydrox is summoned.  Jaydrox says he can't stop them from coming in and that they are clear to pull mobs.<br>
14.  PO leaves rather than try to deal w/2 guilds pulling mobs in fear.<br>
<br>
Yes, IV offered loot to any of our members that stayed.  I believe 4 or 5 took them up on it, prolly some of the guests as well.  Myztika got her epic piece from it.  All of that loot, of course, we would have gotten anyway and had the fun of doing it ourselves.<br>
15.  IV kills CT, loot is 2 cloaks.<br>
16.  Server crashes again.  As I understand it, the cloaks we either not looted or were looted and lost when server reverted to save.  That, however, is hearsay... the rest is not.<br>
<br>
That's PO's version of the events.<br>
