Here is my take on it *not that it matters*.<br>
<br>
1. Vaz is truelly a FFA server now. Hence calander is no longer needed. Its 1st come 1st serve. Posting your raid will just set you up to be jumped by someone else.<br>
<br>
2. Planes are not considered sacred any longer and all spawns inside are FFA. So If you want that boss mob across the zone, you better get to it b4 someone else does.<br>
<br>
3. Named encounters are as always FFA, no news there.<br>
<br>
4. Its survival of the fittest.<br>
<br>
Not defending any guild or slamming any guild here, but it has come down to #4 in all honesty. If you want a span you better be there to engage it 1st, and if you can not handle it... rest assured that other guild watching is going to take it for you.<br>
<br>
Some people wanted a FFA server and some wanted a schedule, well now you have a true FFA server. Hell why should IV offer a guild 1st attempt on a kill? If you want to learn, have fun, raid the big encounters.... come ready to go balls out or go grind for exp.<br>
<br>
This is what Vaz has become and it is no one guilds fault, so why blame IV? Yes the sad truth is the strongest survive, so if a guild wants something they better go for it, rather than working pact's/arrangements.<br>
